OL,3,CConcerns over fairness of new Guernsey
OL,4,CPolice complaints process
OL,6,FDeputy St Pier told ITV News: "If a
OL,7,Fcomplaint is made and filtered out and
OL,8,Fno further work is to be undertaken,
OL,9,Fthe complainant can do nothing further
OL,10,Fabout it and I think that is a matter
OL,11,Ffor concern that warrants further
OL,12,Fconversation."
OL,14,FMeanwhile, Deputy Rob Prow, President
OL,15,Fof Home Affairs, disagrees that the
OL,16,Fnew complaints process is "clumsy" and
OL,17,Fsays an imminent review of police
OL,18,Fprocesses will bring best practices to
OL,19,Fthe island.
