OL,3,CConcerns over fairness of new Guernsey
OL,4,CPolice complaints process
OL,6,FDeputy Prow also responded to Deputy
OL,7,FSt Pier's concerns about a lack of
OL,8,Fopportunity to appeal dismissed
OL,9,Fcomplaints.
OL,11,FHe says that any complaint has to go
OL,12,Fthrough the Police Complaints
OL,13,FCommission before being dismissed,
OL,14,Fwhich he asserts is an independent way
OL,15,Fof reviewing complaints made.
OL,17,FHowever, concerns that the
OL,18,FCommission's links to Home Affairs put
OL,19,Fits independence at risk.
